definitions.definition: Relating to particles that are constituents of the atom , or are smaller than an atom; such as proton , neutron , electron , etc.
Relating to something that is smaller in scale than the diameter of a hydrogen atom.
examples: The electron microscope is able to resolve detail at the subatomic level.
